        <abstract> 
<p>Describes results of his experiments with hollyhocks. Some varieties breed true even though growing near others. This suggests that their pollen is "pre-potent" over that of other varieties, which is not the case with most plants. Asks some questions on which he would be glad to have correspondent work. [See also <hi rend="doubleUnderline">3170</hi>.]</p> 
        </abstract>
